 President Muhammadu Buhari has indicated his readiness to replace his outgoing Ministers without delay. Buhari gave the indication in Abuja, on Friday, during a valedictory session held in honour of the outgoing ministers. Abubakar Malami, Rotimi Amaechi, Godswill Akpabio, Timipre Sylva, Pauline Tallen, Chris Ngige, Uche Ogah, Ogbonnaya Onu and Chukwuemeka Nwajiuba are among the outgoing Ministers. The Ministers were asked to resign from the cabinet following their resolve to seek elective offices in the 2023 general election. 